(43, 8, 12, 40, 5, 14, 14, 'light of the world', 'Light of the World Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being ''the light of the world.'' John 8:12 presents Jesus as the source of light, while Matthew 5:14 extends this idea to his followers, indicating their role in reflecting that light.', 'theme', 0.825, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 12, 18, 33, 28, 28, NULL, 'Light and Deliverance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of light as a source of life and deliverance. John 8:12 speaks of Jesus as the light of the world, while Job 33:28 mentions seeing the light as a form of salvation from the pit.', 'theme', 0.748, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 12, 19, 18, 28, 28, 'light of the world', 'Light and Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of light overcoming darkness. John 8:12 speaks of Jesus as the light of the world, while Psalms 18:28 highlights God''s role in enlightening darkness.', 'theme', 0.734, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 12, 23, 9, 2, 2, 'light of the world', 'Light in Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of light overcoming darkness. John 8:12 declares Jesus as ''the light of the world,'' while Isaiah 9:2 speaks of a great light shining on those in darkness.', 'theme', 0.657, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 12, 23, 60, 1, 3, 'light of the world', 'Light and Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of light overcoming darkness. John 8:12 speaks of Jesus as the light of the world, while Isaiah 60:1-3 describes the glory of the Lord arising amidst darkness. This connection highlights the transformative power of divine light.', 'theme', 0.629, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 13, 43, 5, 31, 47, 'Thou bearest record of thyself', 'Witness and Testimony Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the validity of witness and testimony. In John 8:13, the Pharisees challenge Jesus'' self-testimony, while John 5:31-47 discusses the necessity of external witnesses to affirm his claims.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 14, 43, 13, 3, 3, 'whence I came, and whither I go', 'Connection of Origin and Destination', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' awareness of his origin and destination. In John 8:14, Jesus states he knows ''whence I came, and whither I go,'' while John 13:3 confirms he ''was come from God, and went to God.''', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 14, 43, 16, 28, 28, 'I know whence I came, and whither I go', 'Connection of Origin and Destination', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' awareness of his origin and destination. In John 8:14, he states, ''I know whence I came, and whither I go,'' which parallels John 16:28''s declaration of coming forth from the Father and returning to Him.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 14, 4, 12, 3, 3, NULL, 'Meekness and True Knowledge', 'This connection highlights the theme of true understanding and humility. Jesus asserts his knowledge of his origins and destination, paralleling Moses'' meekness, which reflects a deep understanding of his role and purpose.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
