(43, 8, 40, 43, 8, 37, 38, 'which I have heard of God', 'Connection of Truth and Abraham', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Jesus and Abraham, highlighting the contrast between Abraham''s faithfulness and the audience''s rejection of truth. The mention of seeking to kill Jesus in both verses underscores the conflict between Jesus'' message and the actions of those who claim Abraham as their father.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
