(43, 8, 52, 38, 1, 5, 6, 'If a man keep my saying, he shall never taste of death', 'Eternal Life and Prophets', 'This connection highlights the theme of death and the permanence of God''s words. Both passages address the fate of the prophets and the promise of life through adherence to God''s commands.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 52, 58, 11, 13, 13, 'never taste of death', 'Death and Faith Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of death and faith. In John 8:52, the promise of never tasting death contrasts with Hebrews 11:13, where the faithful die without receiving promises, yet they embrace their faith as pilgrims.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 53, 43, 4, 12, 12, 'greater than our father', 'Comparison of Patriarchs', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of their respective patriarchs, Abraham and Jacob, in the Jewish faith. They question the identity and authority of Jesus in relation to these foundational figures.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 53, 45, 9, 5, 5, 'our father Abraham', 'Connection of Abraham and Christ', 'This connection highlights the significance of Abraham as a foundational figure in the lineage of Christ. Both passages emphasize the relationship between Christ and the patriarchs, with John questioning Christ''s authority in relation to Abraham, while Romans affirms Christ''s descent from him.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 53, 58, 7, 1, 7, 'our father Abraham', 'Abraham''s Significance in Both Passages', 'Both passages emphasize Abraham''s importance, with John 8:53 questioning Jesus'' greatness compared to Abraham, while Hebrews 7:1-7 highlights Abraham''s encounter with Melchisedec, showcasing his role in the priesthood. This connection highlights the significance of Abraham in the context of authority and blessing.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 53, 23, 9, 6, 6, 'Art thou greater than our father Abraham', 'Connection of Authority and Identity', 'This connection highlights the question of identity and authority in both passages. John 8:53 questions Jesus'' greatness compared to Abraham, while Isaiah 9:6 proclaims the child as ''The mighty God,'' emphasizing divine authority.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 53, 40, 12, 6, 6, 'greater than our father Abraham', 'Greater Than Abraham and Temple', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' superiority. Both passages emphasize that Jesus is greater than significant figures and institutions in Jewish tradition, namely Abraham and the temple.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 53, 40, 12, 41, 42, 'greater than our father Abraham', 'Greater Than Abraham and Solomon', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of someone greater than revered figures. In John, Jesus is questioned about His greatness compared to Abraham, while in Matthew, He is identified as greater than Jonah and Solomon.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 53, 43, 5, 18, 18, 'whom makest thou thyself?', 'Connection of Authority and Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the challenge to Jesus'' authority. In John 8:53, the Jews question Jesus'' identity in relation to Abraham, while in John 5:18, they react to His claim of equality with God, indicating a direct confrontation over His self-identification.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 54, 20, 25, 27, 27, 'my honour is nothing', 'Self-Honor and Glory', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of seeking one''s own glory. Jesus points out that true honor comes from God, while Proverbs warns against pursuing personal glory, suggesting it lacks true value.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 54, 43, 8, 50, 50, 'my honour is nothing', 'Connection of Glory and Honor', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of seeking glory not for oneself but from God. Jesus states he does not seek his own glory, and in the following verse, he highlights that it is the Father who honors him.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 54, 61, 1, 17, 17, 'my Father that honoureth me', 'Divine Honor and Glory', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine honor bestowed by God. Both passages emphasize that Jesus receives honor from the Father, linking His identity as the Son with divine approval.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 54, 19, 110, 1, 4, 'my Father that honoureth me', 'Divine Honor and Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine honor, as Jesus refers to the Father honoring Him, paralleling the Lord''s exaltation of the priestly figure in Psalms. Both passages emphasize the relationship between God and His appointed authority.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 54, 43, 16, 14, 15, 'my Father that honoureth me', 'Connection of Honor and Glory', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of divine honor and glory. In John 8:54, Jesus indicates that it is the Father who honors Him, while in John 16:14-15, the Spirit glorifies Jesus by revealing the Father''s truths. This connection highlights the relationship between the Father, the Son, and the Spirit in the act of glorification.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 54, 47, 10, 18, 18, 'my honour is nothing', 'Self-Commendation and Divine Approval', 'Both passages emphasize the idea that self-honor or self-commendation is insufficient. Instead, true honor and approval come from God, highlighting the importance of divine validation over self-promotion.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 54, 19, 2, 6, 12, 'my Father that honoureth me', 'Connection of Honor and Kingship', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine honor and authority. In John 8:54, Jesus speaks of the honor given by the Father, while Psalms 2:6-12 declares God''s establishment of His king, emphasizing the relationship between God and His appointed ruler.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 55, 43, 8, 19, 19, 'know him', 'Knowledge of the Father', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of knowing God. In John 8:55, Jesus asserts his knowledge of the Father, while in John 8:19, he states that the listeners do not know him or the Father. This connection highlights the importance of recognizing Jesus as the key to knowing God.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 55, 43, 7, 28, 29, 'but I know him', 'Knowledge of God Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between Jesus'' knowledge of God and the ignorance of others. In each, Jesus asserts his unique relationship with the Father, highlighting that he knows Him while others do not.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 55, 40, 11, 27, 27, 'I know him', 'Knowledge of the Father and Son', 'Both passages emphasize the unique knowledge of God. John 8:55 states, ''I know him,'' while Matthew 11:27 highlights that ''no man knoweth the Son, but the Father.'' This connection highlights the exclusive relationship between the Father and the Son.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 55, 66, 3, 9, 9, 'I shall be a liar like unto you', 'Connection of Truth and Deception', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of truth versus lies. In John 8:55, Jesus asserts his knowledge of God in contrast to those who lie, while Revelation 3:9 speaks of those who claim to be Jews but are not, highlighting their deception.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 55, 62, 5, 10, 10, 'I know him, and keep his saying', 'Connection of Witness and Knowledge', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowing God and the implications of belief. Both passages emphasize the idea that denying knowledge or belief in God equates to making Him a liar.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 55, 24, 4, 22, 22, NULL, 'Knowledge of God', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of knowing God. In John, the speaker asserts knowledge of God, while Jeremiah describes the people as foolish for not knowing Him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 55, 24, 9, 3, 3, NULL, 'Connection of Knowledge and Truth', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of knowing God and the contrast between truth and lies. John 8:55 highlights the speaker''s knowledge of God, while Jeremiah 9:3 condemns those who do not know Him and speak falsehoods.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 56, 58, 11, 13, 13, 'saw it, and was glad', 'Faith and Vision of Promises', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeing promises from afar. Abraham''s joy in seeing ''my day'' parallels the faithful who ''saw them afar off'' in Hebrews.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 56, 1, 22, 18, 18, 'Your father Abraham rejoiced', 'Abraham''s Promise and Joy', 'This connection highlights Abraham''s role in God''s promise, as seen in both passages. John 8:56 refers to Abraham''s joy in seeing the fulfillment of God''s covenant, while Genesis 22:18 emphasizes the blessing through Abraham''s seed.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 56, 48, 3, 7, 9, NULL, 'Connection of Abraham and Faith', 'This connection highlights the significance of Abraham''s faith in relation to the blessings promised to all nations. Both passages emphasize that those who share in Abraham''s faith are considered his children and are blessed.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 56, 40, 13, 17, 17, 'my day', 'Desire to See Jesus', 'This connection highlights the theme of longing to witness the fulfillment of God''s promises. Both passages emphasize the anticipation of figures like Abraham and the prophets regarding the coming of Jesus and His teachings.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 56, 43, 8, 39, 39, NULL, 'Connection Between Abraham and Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Jesus and Abraham. In John 8:39, Jesus challenges the claim of being Abraham''s children, while in John 8:56, he highlights Abraham''s anticipation of his coming.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 56, 42, 10, 24, 24, 'my day', 'Desire to See Jesus', 'This connection highlights the longing of figures like Abraham, prophets, and kings to witness the fulfillment of God''s promises. Both passages emphasize the joy and anticipation surrounding the revelation of Jesus and His ministry.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
